    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Leen Ammeraal</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/leen-ammeraal-b97b968/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/d/d2/LAmmeraal.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:LAmmeraal.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Leen Ammeraal <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Leen Ammeraal</b>,<br />\na Dutch mathematician and computer scientist, former lecturer at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HU_University_of_Applied_Sciences_Utrecht\">Utrecht University of Applied Sciences</a> (Hogeschool Utrecht), and as computer chess programmer author of the chess engine <a href=\"/Queen_(engine)\" title=\"Queen (engine)\">Queen</a>, and based on Queen, the <a href=\"/Android\" title=\"Android\">Android</a> app <a href=\"/index.php?title=Senior_Chess&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Senior Chess (page does not exist)\">Senior Chess</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. Leen is also author and co-author of programming books about <a href=\"/Cpp\" title=\"Cpp\">C++</a>, <a href=\"/Java\" title=\"Java\">Java</a> and <a href=\"/Graphics_Programming\" title=\"Graphics Programming\">Computer Graphics</a>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leen_Ammeraal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a> (<b>1996</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/~ammeraal/algds.html\">Algorithms and Data Structures in C++</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiley_(publisher)\">Wiley</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a> (<b>1997</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/%7Eammeraal/stlcpp.html\">STL for C++ Programmers</a>.</i> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiley_(publisher)\">Wiley</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a> (<b>2000</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/%7Eammeraal/cppbook.html\">C++ for Programmers</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiley_(publisher)\">Wiley</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.utdallas.edu/%7Ekzhang/\">Kang Zhang</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/%7Eammeraal/grjava2e.html\">Computer Graphics for Java Programmers</a></i>. 2nd edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiley_(publisher)\">Wiley</a> </li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.utdallas.edu/%7Ekzhang/\">Kang Zhang</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/~ammeraal/grjava3e.html\">Computer Graphics for Java Programmers</a></i>. 3rd edition, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Springer_Science%2BBusiness_Media\">Springer</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leen_Ammeraal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leen_Ammeraal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=106507\">Yet another (amateur) chess program</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 18, 2000</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=128608\">Communication between two program versions</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 07, 2000</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=138460\">File name extensions</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 14, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Forsyth-Edwards_Notation\" title=\"Forsyth-Edwards Notation\">Forsyth-Edwards Notation</a>, <a href=\"/Portable_Game_Notation\" title=\"Portable Game Notation\">Portable Game Notation</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=142037\">PV update after retrieval from hash table</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 30, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Principal_Variation\" title=\"Principal Variation\">Principal Variation</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=143234\">Why not store both a lower and an upper bound in a hashtable?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 06, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Transposition_Table\" title=\"Transposition Table\">Transposition Table</a></li></ul>\n<p><b>2001</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=148445\">Bonus points for side to move in qsearch?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 06, 2001&#160;» <a href=\"/Tempo\" title=\"Tempo\">Tempo</a>, <a href=\"/Quiescence_Search\" title=\"Quiescence Search\">Quiescence Search</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=155085\">Is pondering unfair in engine matches on a PC?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 19, 2001&#160;» <a href=\"/Pondering\" title=\"Pondering\">Pondering</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=156376\">Nullmove: when to avoid it?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 28, 2001&#160;» <a href=\"/Null_Move_Pruning\" title=\"Null Move Pruning\">Null Move Pruning</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=179023\">Static Exchange Eval (SEE)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 10, 2001&#160;» <a href=\"/Static_Exchange_Evaluation\" title=\"Static Exchange Evaluation\">Static Exchange Evaluation</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=195809\">Incomplete egtbs can be harmful</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 06, 2001</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=199005\">Conversion to dual positions for EPD testsuites?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 26, 2001&#160;» <a href=\"/Color_Flipping\" title=\"Color Flipping\">Color Flipping</a></li></ul>\n<p><b>2002</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=209546\">Counting attacked squares: how?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 24, 2002</li></ul>\n<p><b>2005</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=412241\">Queen 3.00</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 17, 2005</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leen_Ammeraal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=51836\">Queen 4.03a: GUI improved</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, June 17, 2011</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leen_Ammeraal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/%7Eammeraal/\">Leen Ammeraal homepage</a></li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/%7Eammeraal/chess.html\">Leen Ammeraal - Queen</a></dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/leen-ammeraal-b97b968/\">Leen Ammeraal | LinkedIn</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/developer?id=Leen+Ammeraal&amp;hl=en_US\">Android Apps</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Leen Ammeraal</a> on <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_Play\">Google Play</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leen_Ammeraal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/leen-ammeraal-b97b968/\">Leen Ammeraal | LinkedIn</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/~ammeraal/chess.html\">Leen Ammeraal - Queen</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://home.planet.nl/~ammeraal/english.html\">Leen Ammeraal (English)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=106520\">Re: (Offtopic)</a> by <a href=\"/Gian-Carlo_Pascutto\" title=\"Gian-Carlo Pascutto\">Gian-Carlo Pascutto</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 18, 2000</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301105232\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.016 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.017 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 83/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 174/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/4